Nykaa, a beauty and fashion ecommerce company has been pulled down by Kotak Institutional Equities in this quarter as the company faces issues related to the increase in fulfilment cost and competition from the players in the quick commerce space. Sunny Leone turned her passion for beauty into a bold entrepreneurial move. In 2018, she invested ‚Çπ10 lakh of her own money to launch StarStruck, a cruelty-free, PETA-certified cosmetics brand. Unlike many celebrity labels, this wasn‚Äôt just a name attached to a product ‚Äî Sunny was deeply involved in every detail, from packaging to product creation.

Today, StarStruck offers 260+ products‚Äîfrom lipsticks and eyeliners to foundations‚Äîbuilt around ethics, affordability, and inclusivity. Despite the highly competitive beauty market and challenges around her public image, Sunny grew the brand without external investors, proving herself as a determined entrepreneur with grit and vision.

Now a ‚Çπ10 Cr+ global brand, StarStruck is available across India, North America, the UK, and Europe, with plans to expand into fragrances, innerwear, and offline retail.

From being India‚Äôs most Googled celebrity to building one of its most authentic beauty brands, Sunny Leone‚Äôs journey shows how glam and grit together can create lasting success.
